f(x)=\begin{pmatrix}1/4 & 0 & 1/2 \\ 0 & 1/3 & 0\\ -1/2 & 0 & 1/4 \end{pmatrix}\begin{pmatrix}x_1 \\ x_2\\ x_3 \end{pmatrix}, \qquad\forall x=\begin{pmatrix}x_1 \\ x_2\\ x_3 \end{pmatrix} \in \Bbb R^3 
A: \mathbb{R}^3\to  \mathbb{R}^3
\lambda_{\mathrm{max}}(A^T A)
A^TA
1
\|f(x)\| = \|Ax\| \leq \|A\| \|x\|,
 \|A\| = \sup_{x\in \mathbb{R}^3}\frac{\|Ax\|}{\|x\|}. 
  \|A\|  = \sqrt{\lambda_{\mathrm{max}}(A^T A)}, 
\lambda_{\mathrm{max}} = 5/16
\|A\| = \sqrt{5}/4 < 1
